# Defensive: package.json `files` field is the canonical allowlist for what
# ships in the tarball. This .npmignore is a belt-and-braces guard against
# future npm-default changes that might silently include any of these paths.
#
# Keep this list aligned with the project structure — if you add a new top-level
# directory that should NOT ship, add it here too.

.planning/
.claude/
.github/
test/
node_modules/
.npmrc
.editorconfig
.eslintrc*
.prettierrc*
*.log
*.swp
.DS_Store
.idea/
.vscode/
.ci-test/
.ci-safety/
docs/
